{"name": "stablehash", "metadata": {"name": "stablehash", "version": "0.2.1", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules", "Topic :: Utilities"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Stable hashing of Python data structures across separate processes and platforms.", "upload_time": 1726354256}, "documentation": ["# stablehash\n\nThe `stablehash` module provides a \"pure\" hash function that is stable across Python processes and runs. This is in\ncontrast to the builtin `hash()` function, which may return a different value for the same input in separate\ninvokations even with the Python version.\n\nWe support most Python built-in types, including mutable types such as `list` and `dict`, as well as dataclasses. The\ndefault internal hash algorithm is Blake2b, but this can be changed by passing a different `hashlib` algorithm to the\n`stablehash` function.\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\nfrom stablehash import stablehash\n\nassert stablehash({\"key\": \"value\"}, algorithm=\"md5\").hexdigest() == 'd5994850379366e314563ea555532052'\n```\n\n## API\n\n### `stablehash(obj=..., *, algorithm=\"blake2b\")`\n\nReturns a `hashlib`-compatible object with the given algorithm and the hash of the given object. The algorithm must be\none of the algorithms supported by `hashlib`.\n\n### `stablehash.update(obj)`\n\nUpdates the hash with the given object. If the object is not supported, a `TypeError` is raised.\n\n### `stablehash.digest()`\n\nReturns the digest of the hash as a bytes object.\n\n### `stablehash.hexdigest()`\n\nReturns the digest of the hash as a string object.\n\n## Supported types\n\nThe following types are supported:\n\n- `None`\n- `bool`\n- `int`\n- `float`\n- `str`\n- `bytes`\n- `tuple`\n- `list`\n- `set`\n- `frozenset`\n- `dict`\n- `@dataclass` objects\n- `datetime` objects (`datetime`, `date`, `time` and `timedelta`)\n- `uuid.UUID`\n- Picklable objects (e.g. those that implement `__getstate__()`)\n- `type` objects (by their full qualified name)\n"], "modules": [{"name": "stablehash", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "stablehash.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stablehash._sentinel", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "stablehash.stablehash", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "stablehash.stablehash.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "algorithm", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Create a new {class}`stablehash` instance.\n\n```\nparam data\n\nData to hash.\n\nparam algorithm\n\nThe hash algorithm to use. Defaults to \"blake2b\".\n```\n"]}, {"name": "stablehash.stablehash.update", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "x", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Update the hash with the specified object."]}, {"name": "stablehash.stablehash.digest", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bytes", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bytes", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Return the digest of the objects hashed so far."]}, {"name": "stablehash.stablehash.hexdigest", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Return the hex digest of the objects hashed so far."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A fast and stable hash function for Python objects."]}], "exports": [{"name": "stablehash.Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": null}}, {"name": "stablehash.tokenize", "xref": {"fqname": "stablehash._tokenize.tokenize", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "stablehash.__init__test", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "stablehash.__init__test.test__stablehash", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "stablehash.__init__test.MyDataclass", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "stablehash.__init__test.MyDataclass.a", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stablehash.__init__test.MyDataclass.b", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "stablehash.__init__test.Picklable", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "stablehash.__init__test.Picklable.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "a", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, 